.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref> It is the follow-up to .<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%223%22])">3</ref>
<sec>
<st>
Story</st>
<p>
 
The game has protagonist <link>
Gabe Logan</link> sent on a mission to retrieve a package containing a dangerous new technology within a ship's cargo hold. While there, Gabe discovers that the ship has been ambushed and the package stolen. Robert Cordell, the governmental bureaucrat in charge of the <administrative_unit wordnetid="108077292" confidence="0.8">
<agency wordnetid="108337324" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../997/11734997.xml">
IPCA</link></agency>
</administrative_unit>
, is shutting down the agency due to the failed mission and because Gabe's long-time partner, <link>
Lian Xing</link>, has disappeared and is suspected of being a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../203/291203.xml">
double agent</link>.</p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
Gameplay</st>
<p>

<it>Logan's Shadow</it> is played from a third-person perspective. With the <artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
<instrumentality wordnetid="103575240" confidence="0.8">
<engine wordnetid="103287733" confidence="0.8">
<motor wordnetid="103789946" confidence="0.8">
<device wordnetid="103183080" confidence="0.8">
<machine wordnetid="103699975" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../605/857605.xml">
Havok</link></machine>
</device>
</motor>
</engine>
</instrumentality>
</artifact>
 physics, enemies and objects will react realistically to gunfire and other means of interaction. </p>
<p>

<it>Logan's Shadow</it> features new weapons and gameplay mechanics. These include additions to the cover system such as side-to-side movement, leaning, and blind fire around obstacles and corners, an advanced melee system that allows Gabe to use enemies as human shields, underwater combat, and the ability to command other characters.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%224%22])">4</ref><ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%225%22])">5</ref></p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
Multiplayer</st>
<p>

Players can now play as new factions in five game modes, two of which are new to the franchise. The new modes revealed are Sabotage and Retrieval. Sabotage pits two teams against each other as they try to locate bomb codes and arm the other team's nuclear warhead and guard it to prevent them from disarming their bomb until the timer runs out, while Retrieval has players trying to retrieve a beacon from the enemy's base and return it to their base to score a point. Your team's beacon must be at your base to be able to score. Returning modes are <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../070/4675070.xml">
Deathmatch</link>, <link>
Team Deathmatch</link>, and Rogue Agent.</p>

<ss1>
<st>
Combat Ops</st>

<p>

<indent level="1">

<it>Main article: </it>
</indent>
<b>Combat Ops</b> is a multiplayer-exclusive game available from the Playstation Network. A playable sneak preview is accessible from the <it>Logan's Shadow</it> main menu. Combat Ops was originally discovered in late August 2007 when the <it>Logan's Shadow</it> demo <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../690/1106690.xml">
UMD</link> data was explored using various tools. Among the demo files was a .prx for Combat Ops, which, when used to replace the normal demo .prx, launched a beta version of Combat Ops.</p>
<p>

Combat Ops allows players to edit pre-existing maps and adding their own objects, weapons, objectives, spawn points, and other information. Players can customize the names of the factions and choose what factions they want for their "mission". A mission is an edited map that can be taken online or into <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../704/168704.xml">
Ad-hoc</link> to share and play with others. Combat Ops will feature exclusive skins (such as a goose costume) and content not available in previous <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../644/1711644.xml">
Syphon Filter</link></it> games. </p>
<p>

Combat Ops is now available for download from the <weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://store.playstation.com">
Playstation Store's PC web site</weblink>.</p>

</ss1>
</sec>
<sec>
<st>
Reception</st>
<p>

IGN called <it>Logan's Shadow</it> it "a worthy successor to <it>Dark Mirror</it>" and that it has "a deeper experience that surpasses <it>Dark Mirror</it> in every way", and also refers to it as one of the best PSP games of the year.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%226%22])">6</ref>. Gamespy gives credit to Greg Rucka for writing an immersive and complex storyline.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%227%22])">7</ref></p>

